Use a grouped line chart when you have multiple groupings—each with one important secondary grouping representing an ordered set of data—and one value to show.
For example, to see monthly leads by lead source in a report, set record count as the Y-axis, created month as the X-axis, and source as the Groupings value. The chart displays a line for each source, connecting that source's record count totals for each month. Each line spans the earliest to the latest month containing data.
Salesforce does not plot missing (null) values. If a missing value occurs in the middle of a data set, Salesforce displays a gap in the line.
title: Grouped Line Chart in Salesforce Analytics
